snippet: Briton Andy Murray will take over from Novak Djokovic as world number one when the rankings are updated on Monday after his Paris Masters semi-final opponent Milos Raonic withdrew with a leg injury on Saturday....
lead_paragraph: Briton Andy Murray will take over from Novak Djokovic as world number one when the rankings are updated on Monday after his Paris Masters semi-final opponent Milos Raonic withdrew with a leg injury on Saturday.

headline.print_headline: Andy Murray Is New World No. 1 After Raonic Pulls Out Injured
headline.main: Andy Murray Is New World No. 1 After Raonic Pulls Out Injured
